{{Quote|Fluggy will undergo the procedure tomorrow and should be back at practice with the team in five or six days, [...] His original arm will likely be donated to the hi-lo hall of fame.|Guire Sleazebaggano|<ref name="HNN">{{HoloNetNewsWeb|51|sports/13411_2.html|Flugg Opts for New Arm}}</ref>}}
'''Guire Sleazebaggano''' was the agent of [[hi-lo ball]] player [[Garcy Flugg]]. After Flugg missed fifteen matches in two [[Standard year/Legends|years]] due to chronic elbow injuries, Sleazebaggano informed the [[HoloNet News/Legends|HoloNet News]] of Flugg's decision to replace his injured [[Limb/Legends|arm]] with a [[Cybernetics/Legends|mechanical]] one.

